longBusinessSummary: MISC Berhad provides energy-related maritime solutions and services worldwide. The company operates through LNG (liquefied natural gas), Petroleum, Offshore, Heavy Engineering, and Others segments. It owns and operates LNG carriers; petroleum tankers; and floating storage and offloading, mobile offshore production, and semi-submersible floating production systems, as well as floating production, storage, and offloading units. The company is also involved in the provision of marine and heavy engineering services, including engineering, procurement, construction, installation, and commissioning services for offshore and onshore construction; undertakes conversion works; and marine repair, refurbishment, upgradation, and life extension of vessels and rigs. In addition, it offers maritime education and training services for seamen and maritime personnel; port and terminal services; integrated marine services, such as fleet management and operation, crew management and manning, and dry-docking management services, as well as project management services for new build construction and conversion projects. Further, the company operates and manages the Sungai Udang Port; offers sludge disposal management and financing services; and owns properties. It operates a fleet of approximately 110 owned and in-chartered LNG, petroleum, and product vessels; 14 floating production systems; and 2 LNG floating storage units with a combined deadweight tonnage capacity of approximately 16 million tonnes. The company was incorporated in 1968 and is headquartered in Kuala Lumpur, Malaysia. MISC Berhad is a subsidiary of Petroliam Nasional Berhad.
